FT  25 OCT 93 / Disabled workers
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
ONLY about one in 20 employers come close to meeting the legal requirement
to have registered disabled people making up 3 per cent of their workforce
if they employ more than 20 people, a survey by the Institute of Manpower
Studies has found. The number more than doubles if non-registered disabled
people are included.
