<HEADLINE>
FT  25 OCT 93 / Cedras to meet Haitian PM
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CANUTE JAMES
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   KINGSTON, JAMAICA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
MR Robert Malval, prime minister of Haiti, and Gen Raoul Cedras, the head of
the army, will meet today in an effort to end the country's political
crisis, five days before the scheduled, but unlikely, return of Mr
Jean-Bertrand Aristide, the exiled president.
In a meeting on Saturday between Mr Malval and Gen Cedras, the army leader
said he was willing to step down to allow the president's return, but he and
other military officers wanted parliamentary ratification of a general
amnesty for all who led and supported the coup against Mr Aristide two years
ago.
Gen Cedras also repeated the army's desire for a broader-based government to
include civilian supporters of the coup. Mr Malval had indicated a
willingness to compromise on this, but Mr Aristide's aides have raised
objections.
Mr Dante Caputo, the UN mediator, said on Saturday he had received from
pro-military parliamentarians 'important' new proposals for ending the
crisis. Diplomats said yesterday that the proposals coincided with the
demands which Gen Cedras is making of Mr Malval.
</TEXT>
