FT  25 OCT 93 / Liechtenstein poll
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   VADUZ
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Early results in yesterday's Liechtenstein election showed the senior party
in the principality's ruling coalition was likely to lose its majority to
its alliance partner, Reuter reports from Vaduz. Based on preliminary
results from five out of 11 constituencies, the centrist Fatherland Union
appeared likely to regain the majority it lost earlier this year to the
right wing.
