<HEADLINE>
FT  25 OCT 93 / IRA blast hits main London-West railway line
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Up to 40,000 commuters faced disruption today after an IRA bomb at Reading
damaged the British Rail main line between the West and London last night,
police said. No casualties were reported.
The blast, which followed a coded warning, came hours after the army
disabled bombs at Reading and Basingstoke railway stations. BR laid on
contingency plans for commuters if the route remained closed this morning.
Guildford station was also shut after a warning, and a controlled explosion
was carried out at Waterloo, but police said the item was not a bomb.
