<HEADLINE>
FT  23 OCT 93 / World Commodities Prices: Spices
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The pepper market suffered from lack of activity throughout the week as a
consequence of which prices tended slightly easier, reports Man Producten.
More offers of black pepper from brazil appeared in the market at slightly
reduced prices. Other origins were not active at all. Black pepper for
prompt delivery in Europe was valued between USDollars 1,600 and Dollars
1,675 a tonne, ex-warehouse. White pepper offers were scarce at unchanged
prices of about Dollars 3,300 a tonne, cif, and Dollars 3,375-Dollars 3,400
for spot material. Demand was negligible.
</TEXT>
