<HEADLINE>
FT  23 OCT 93 / UK Company News: Delian Lloyd's trust aims to raise Pounds
50m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD LAPPER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
DELIAN LLOYD'S Investment Trust yesterday became the seventh new Lloyd's
investment company to publish a pathfinder prospectus. Delian is seeking a
full listing through a placing by Hill Samuel, writes Richard Lapper.
Delian aims to raise Pounds 50m, allowing it to provide up to Pounds 100m in
capacity to between 40 and 50 syndicates. RF Kershaw, the independent
members' agent, will act as a licensed Lloyd's adviser, while the investment
portfolio will be managed by Foreign &amp; Colonial Management.
'We have deliberately chosen a Lloyd's adviser which is independent of the
agents who manage syndicates, in order to avoid conflicts of interest that
are otherwise inevitable,' said Lord Stewartby, chairman.
Earlier this week SG Warburg and Samuel Montagu also published pathfinder
prospectuses for new trusts. The London Insurance Market Investment Trust,
the biggest trust announced to date, is seeking to raise Pounds 280m.
Applications for shares in Limit will be for a minimum of 1,000 shares at an
offer price of 100p per share.
