<HEADLINE>
FT  23 OCT 93 / Abramsky to head new BBC service
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RAYMOND SNODDY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MS JENNY ABRAMSKY has been appointed controller of the new BBC radio news
and sport network, due to be launched on March 28 next year, Raymond Snoddy
writes.
Ms Abramsky has been editor of news and current affairs for BBC radio since
1987.
Mr Mike Lewis, head of sports and outside broadcasts for BBC radio, is to be
deputy controller.
The appointments coincide with the introduction of a new management
structure in BBC news and current affairs combining radio and television
resources.
Mr Peter Bell, now editor of television news programmes, will become
responsible for all news output. BBC Enterprises said yesterday that deals
worth Pounds 10m were negotiated during the media market at Cannes,
including the sale of Thatcher: The Downing Street Years.
